Acer Nitro V16 Advanced Control Driver (qapkyy_qy)
===================================================

The qapkyy_qy kernel driver module provides an advanced hardware control
interface explicitly tailored for the Acer Nitro V16 (ANV16-71) laptop platform
on Linux architectures. This implementation functions as an isolated kernel module to
completely decouple control mechanics from the native upstream acer-wmi
subsystem, removing resource execution conflicts.

This driver introduces programmatic controls directly missing under native
Linux platform frameworks, including physical firmware-bound thermal profiles,
direct fan hardware monitoring/speed automation, and non-volatile battery
charging health limits.

1. System Prerequisites
-----------------------

    Before executing the compiled automated structures, verify that your
    target Linux operating system environment includes the mandatory platform
    build headers:

    * Linux Kernel Version: 6.x or newer recommended.
    * Base System Packages: linux-headers (or linux-devel depending on
      distribution) and standard build essentials (gcc, make, openssl).
2. Installation (assume secure boot active.)
--------------------------------------------

    chmod +x setup.sh
    bash setup.sh

    * To examine target unit execution tracking logs:
      sudo systemctl status qapkyy_qy.service

